[normal]In 
[normal]2007, a
[normal] team of climate scientists from the Met Office wrote a paper “
[normal]Improved Surface Temperature Prediction for the Coming Decade from a Global Climate Model
[normal]” 
[normal]using their new modeling system 
[normal]which forecast
[normal]:-
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Ms.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Vicky Pope
[normal] of the Met Office
[normal] gave a talk on these predictions, 
[normal]stating t
[normal]hat
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]“these are very strong statements about what will happen over the next 10 years.”
[normal]  
[normal]These predictions are wrong - there has been no warming at all since 2004; 
[normal]none 
[normal]of the years since 2009
[normal] h
[normal]ave broken the record of 1998 according to HADCRUT3 data
[normal]. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Physics Nobel Prize Winner Richard Feynman’s inaugural lecture at Caltech in 1974 “Cargo cult science”
[normal] provides a useful concept.  If we were dealing with real science which hypothesizes then tests the hypothesis against reality, the abysmal record of the models in projecting/predicting/forecasting 
[normal](
[normal]or whatever word 
[normal]one cares 
[normal]to choose
[normal])
[normal] would have led to chucking them out
[normal] 
[normal]and going back to the hypothesis drawing board. 
[normal] The 
[normal]Met Office would be eating humble pie for the aforementioned misforecast (and perhaps also for recent seasonal 
[normal]mis
[normal]forecasts
[normal]).  But no, it is telling us the temperature pause is a temporary phenomena and normal warming will be continued soon in line with its 
[normal](CO2 
[normal]d
[normal]riven
[normal])
[normal] models. We
[normal] are dealing with politicized and too often fanciful climate science whose models have in many
[normal] 
[normal]mind
[normal]s
[normal] become a pseudo reality – climate models are real cargo cult science.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]As Professor Richard Lindzen of MIT commented
[normal] in a seminar he gave in the House of Commons last year
[normal] “Climate science is immature.  It cannot forecast the past, let alone the future”.  And he commented of the Fifth Assessment Report
[normal]:-
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]“I think that 
[normal]the latest IPCC report
[normal] has truly sunk to level of hilarious incoherence.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal] They are proclaiming increased confidence in their models as the discrepancies between their models and observations increase…”
[normal]&#xa0;
